                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.00/590: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">De Lambert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-07-14T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 14, 1925—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>19. Your 28, July 10, 4 p.m. Pending crystalization of present political
                    situation you are instructed carefully to avoid any action <pb facs="0147"
                        n="65" xml:id="pg_65"/> which might be construed as recognition of the
                    regime actually functioning in Ecuador. Communication with the <hi rend="italic"
                        >de facto</hi> authorities should be friendly but personal and strictly
                    informal omitting use of titles such as Minister for Foreign Affairs, etc.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
